<statement>
<p>58 is what percent of 40? <fillin characters="4"/><percent/> </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>145</li></ul></p><p>Because we are asked for 58 of 40 we calculate,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\frac{{58}}{{40}}={1.45}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1.45}\times{100}={145}</m>.</p>
<p>The result is greater than 100<percent/>, because the new amount is greater than the original amount.</p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>